Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.55,0:00:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,the same as practicing religion.\NReligion is one thing. God is not
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.23,0:00:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,something else. God is a generic term\Ngeneric term for divinity. It is not a
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.39,0:01:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,religion.\NAll right. The importance of the 200s
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.84,0:01:06.47,Default,,0,0,0,,then let's just go over there. I thought\NI'd make a whole slide of it because it
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.47,0:01:12.40,Default,,0,0,0,,is so important.\NNo, the 200s here. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.40,0:01:18.79,Default,,0,0,0,,What do we call it? Virtues. Yeah.\NOkay.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.79,0:01:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Transcending then the limitations of the\Nego and the roadway to enlightenment is
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.72,0:01:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,simple is very simple.\NThe basic the basic characteristics of a
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.88,0:01:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,person has crossed over 200 let's say\Ncould be stated simply
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.11,0:01:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,good will towards all. Goodwill good\Nwill towards all.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.88,0:01:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Practice that in all\Nin all things. Kindness, respect for
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.88,0:01:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,life.\NRespect for life, respect for the rights
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.47,0:01:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,of others, consideration.\NNo great requirement. That doesn't mean
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.88,0:02:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,leaving the world and sitting\Ncross-legged, shaving your head and
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.84,0:02:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,doing all those strange things.\NIt means you go through the world
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.31,0:02:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,as though you are part of a certain\Nfield which is considerate of others
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.84,0:02:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,automatically considerate of others. And\Nwhen it's inconsiderate it corrects
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.48,0:02:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,itself.\NThe person who's gone over 200 when
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.92,0:02:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,they're inconsiderate it's not okay with\Nthem. They go to bed that night. They
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.28,0:02:32.87,Default,,0,0,0,,hear their mind trying to justify what\Nthey said, but
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.87,0:02:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,part of their mind keeps nagging them,\Nkeeps nagging them because it was not a
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.72,0:02:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,kind remark. It was, etc. So now this is\Nthe new paradigm which we live up to. It
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.64,0:02:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,sounds very basic. Any one of these will\Ntake you all the way to enlightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.48,0:02:54.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Take anything off this chart and\Npractice it incessantly,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.87,0:02:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,constantly, run the clock with no\Nexceptions. Any one of these will take
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.56,0:03:03.59,Default,,0,0,0,,you all the way. First one is\Navailability.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.59,0:03:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The availability of what? To be present.\NTo be present.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.51,0:03:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You walk into a restaurant and when she\Nnever looks at you. She writes it down.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.80,0:03:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't fault her for it. She's not\Npresent.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.28,0:03:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The next one comes in, smiles.\NInstantly, there's a connection. They're
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.84,0:03:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,present. Present.\NThe old truck stop. You the witches
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.12,0:03:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,always called you sweetheart. And the\Nold truckers always call them honey. You
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.00,0:03:38.31,Default,,0,0,0,,have the same thing, honey. Yep.\NSweetheart.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.31,0:03:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You see how the politically correct\Nperson would be offended by that?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.36,0:03:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a style of connectedness. A style\Nof connectedness. It was a way of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.00,0:03:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,lovingness actually lovingness\Nin and caringness an expression of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.20,0:03:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,concern for your fellow human being\Nwhich you kind of have sweetheart same
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.79,0:04:02.79,Default,,0,0,0,,as usual. Yeah any bud\Nsounds gruff sort of macho world of you
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.79,0:04:09.12,Default,,0,0,0,,know the trucker but it you you get the\Nsense of it you get the sense of it
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.12,0:04:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,so they're available to each other\Nresponsive to each other acknowledge
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.36,0:04:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,each other's importance in their life.\NYeah. And when you stop back at the same
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.51,0:04:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,truck stop, your favorite waitress isn't\Nthere. You feel disappointed. Oh well,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.47,0:04:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,you all sit in her section. You know,\Nthere's a certain affectionateness then.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.04,0:04:36.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So the person is available. They're\Npresent. They're present.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.63,0:04:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,But I felt this morning when I felt\Nsomething go out in the unconscious. I
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.96,0:04:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,felt the being present pull back into\Nthinking this, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.24,0:04:50.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Because thinking this is not present.\NBeing present. Thinkingness is thinking
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.40,0:04:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,this.\NAnd I felt the energy pull out of being
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.56,0:05:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,present to thinkingness into it clicked\Ninto the left brain. Being considerate
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.47,0:05:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,of others is merely being polite and\Nthoughtful. Being generous.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.96,0:05:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Being decent. Just being decent. You\Nthink that's difficult?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.88,0:05:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,MTV. That's decent. in the gangster rock\Nmusic talking about killing, murder,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.68,0:05:26.32,Default,,0,0,0,,raping, drugs, suicide,\Nall kinds of sexual deviations, etc.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.32,0:05:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,One just doesn't have to make it bad.\NOne doesn't have to call it wicked. One
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.60,0:05:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't have to call it evil. One\Ndoesn't have to get epopletic about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.80,0:05:40.88,Default,,0,0,0,,One doesn't have to get bombastic about\Nit, pontificate about it. You just don't
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.88,0:05:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,go there.\NSomehow it's no longer appealing. No
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.88,0:05:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,longer appealing. The energy of the\Ncasino just doesn't grab you anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.96,0:05:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The glamour, the clicking, the sounds,\Nthe magic, the ambiance.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.68,0:05:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see why it's attractive. It's\Nnot like you make it wrong. And you can
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.44,0:06:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,see if you're really bored,\Nyou put in $20 in the nickel machine and
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.63,0:06:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,when it's out, my god, it'll be two in\Nthe morning when you finally get out of
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.52,0:06:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,there.\NAll right. So you can do it for lots of
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.68,0:06:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,reasons. Social curiosity what's and you\Nknow casinos don't calibrate over 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.24,0:06:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. Just being decent then to be\Ndecent to be responsible. This is so
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.72,0:06:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,difficult for so many people because the\Nkid in us always wants to deny
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.08,0:06:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,responsibility.\NIt's afraid of guilt and penance. And of
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.00,0:06:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,course that comes out of a culture in\Nwhich we look for the guilty party
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.19,0:06:47.68,Default,,0,0,0,,right after the\Ndisaster where the insulation fell off
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.68,0:06:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the space machine whatever they call\Nthat thing. They're right away looking
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.16,0:06:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,for who's responsible. Happily they\Ndiscovered it was the totality of the
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.72,0:07:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,field and not some poor\Nperson that you could then persecute.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.72,0:07:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So the person then spiritually committed\Ntends to be reliable.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.63,0:07:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,If you ask them to do something, they do\Nit. And if they can't, they tell you
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.31,0:07:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,they can't do it. You know, I can't be\Nthere. They don't just leave you
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.00,0:07:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,standing on the street corner. They\Ndon't tell you they mailed the letter
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.44,0:07:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,when it's still in the car. They just\Nsay, "No, I forgot it. It's still in the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.36,0:07:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,car." The willing to take\Nresponsibility, uh, is integrity. So
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.36,0:07:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,integrity at 200 is so critical.\NThey're willing to be honest about the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.47,0:07:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,thing. Well, people can't be honest\Nabout the thing if they're going to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.16,0:07:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,persecute themselves and vilify\Nthemselves for having made a mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.28,0:07:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So, consequently, we have to have an\Neasier conscience to begin conscience to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.59,0:07:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,begin with. You can make a mistake and\Nyou don't have to hit the bottom of the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.91,0:07:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,barrel about that. It's just nothing.\NSo, integrous people are reliable. They
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.84,0:08:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,tend to be honest.\NWhat about hard work? What does hard
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.52,0:08:07.91,Default,,0,0,0,,work mean? All it means is that we put\Nforth the energy of our presence to the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.91,0:08:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,best capacity that we have in everything\Nthat we do.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.44,0:08:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Integrous people are integrous pretty\Nmuch round the clock. They may have
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.68,0:08:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,specific limitations, but if you ask\Nthem to take out the garbage, they're
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.19,0:08:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,just as likely to do that as they are to\Npay the day's bills as they are to stop
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.44,0:08:32.15,Default,,0,0,0,,at the supermarket and get something\Nand refill the and refill that car with
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.15,0:08:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,oil. They're going to be dependable\Nthat you can count on. If you can't
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.80,0:08:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,count on people, then they're an\Naggravation. They're detrimental in your
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.71,0:08:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,life. They're detrimental in your life.\NAnd people that are not reliable drive
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.27,0:08:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you crazy.\NHonesty, hard work then is just an
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.72,0:08:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,automatic consequence of the energy.\NPeople 200 and up have higher energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.60,0:09:04.16,Default,,0,0,0,,They tend to be moral. Now, their morals\Nmay differ from yours. Their moral
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.16,0:09:09.04,Default,,0,0,0,,system may differ, but they're still\Nmoral. So if on the other side of the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.04,0:09:12.95,Default,,0,0,0,,world they consider things moral or\Nimmoral that we do not agree with, they
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.95,0:09:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,are nevertheless being moral in their\Nown eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.04,0:09:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,People that are above 200 tend to be\Nwarm and they also tend to bring that
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.83,0:09:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,forth in others. So if you're a warm\Nfriendly person, you say, "How was your
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.12,0:09:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,trip to Cincinnati?" they'll say, "Oh,\Nthe people there were very nice."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.92,0:09:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The people were there were very nice.\NPeople below 200 do not think the people
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.60,0:09:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,in Cincinnati are nice. They'll tell you\Nthey're cold, self-centered, selfish,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.68,0:09:49.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and will treat you.\NAnd for them, that's probably true.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.60,0:09:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The people there probably do hate them.\NI never thought of that. Never thought
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.88,0:09:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,of that. Yeah. So, the warm person then\Ntends to bring forth warmth in in
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.36,0:10:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,others. What are you going to have for\Nbreakfast? Sugar p plum. And he says,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.60,0:10:08.95,Default,,0,0,0,,"Same thing, sweetheart." So the trucker\Nand the waitress, you know, have a warm
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.95,0:10:14.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and yet it remains moral and there's a\Nmutual kindness, a mutual kindness to be
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.32,0:10:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,kind to all living things. Now, one of\Nthe things that's important to be kind
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.44,0:10:24.95,Default,,0,0,0,,to is yourself.\NAnd that's why you have to give your ego
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.95,0:10:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,a name. The bad side of you, the shadow\Nside of you,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.07,0:10:34.95,Default,,0,0,0,,what I think young side of this book\Ncalled the shadow side.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.95,0:10:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Give it a pet name that brings it closer\Nto reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.60,0:10:44.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Your own human nature deserves at least\Nas much respect as Coco
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.56,0:10:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,or Alex\Nor the cow with a running nose.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.36,0:10:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't kick the cow with a running\Nnose.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.88,0:11:02.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So at least be kind to your inner ego\Ninstead of vilifying it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.07,0:11:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't get over being a cow with\Npenance.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.88,0:11:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I can do the rosary century after\Ncentury and its nose still runs.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.32,0:11:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the running nose of guilt, self-penance,\Nand self-hatred. You understand how sin
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.00,0:11:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and guilt and penance bring up\Nselfhatred?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.00,0:11:34.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Self-hatred brings up hatred and\Nintolerance of others.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.72,0:11:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,This brings up intolerance and\Npersecution of others who think
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.76,0:11:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,differently than you do. That which is\Ncruel to itself is innately cruel to all
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.07,0:11:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,of life.\NThat which is cruel to itself, that
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.16,0:11:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,which wallows in penance,\Nwatch out for it. First of all, don't
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.27,0:11:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,have a sense of humor, which is a\Nterrible, which is a sign of extreme
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.04,0:12:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,danger.\NThat which is gilly and you see gets
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.68,0:12:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,obsessive, compulsive, and it has no\Nsense of humor.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.07,0:12:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Those who have a sense of humor, watch\Nthem.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.39,0:12:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,warm, kind, helpful to others\Nautomatically.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.24,0:12:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The Boy Scouts of America, I think, is a\Ngreat training in the Girl Scouts of
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.68,0:12:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,America. I guess you're not allowed to\Ncall them Boys and Girls anymore. The
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.07,0:12:28.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the young people of America, whatever\Nthey call them, Boy Scouts of America.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.63,0:12:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, starts with moral principles,\Nyou know, and the moral principles are
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.63,0:12:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,are designed to be honorable, to be\Nhonorable, to be helpful, respectful,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.12,0:12:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,all the basic virtues. All the basic\Nvirtues. So, I can't see vilifying an
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.83,0:12:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,organization\Nthat stands for the basic virtues. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.44,0:12:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Kind, helpful, diligent, easygoing.\NEasygoing is the hardest one I think for
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.51,0:13:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,people to get.\NEasy going because when you deal with
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.27,0:13:09.83,Default,,0,0,0,,loss or loss of potential gain the\Nperson t in our society
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.83,0:13:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,uh\Nit's hard to be kind to yourself to be
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.07,0:13:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,warm kinds\Nand well-meaning towards yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.60,0:13:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So easy goinging is a style. Is a style.\NRemember in the 12step groups it says
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.68,0:13:34.63,Default,,0,0,0,,easy does it. You know what I mean?\NSomebody ran off with your car. Well,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.63,0:13:38.72,Default,,0,0,0,,look, the insurance company will pay for\Nit or I'll buy another. I'll borrow
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.72,0:13:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,money. It isn't the end of the world.\NSo, you don't commit suicide. Everything
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.39,0:13:47.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that comes down the pike.\NYou don't commit emotional suicide by
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.04,0:13:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,getting disturbed over everything. Easy\Ndoes it. Live and let live, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.44,0:13:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,are easy. easygoing.\NThe easygoing person is therefore
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.72,0:14:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,thoughtful. They tend to be persistent.\NThey tend to be open. They're
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.68,0:14:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,approachable, approachable,\Napproachable.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.12,0:14:10.95,Default,,0,0,0,,They tend to be tolerant of others. They\Ntend to be calm, dependable,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.95,0:14:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,genuine, meaning if you say you're going\Nto be that or do that to do that. What
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.72,0:14:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,does respectable mean? It doesn't means\Nprissy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.39,0:14:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, when I first first time I went\Nto Europe, I was shocked that the men's
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.32,0:14:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and women's rooms in France and Paris\Nwere were one and the same and just they
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.68,0:14:34.16,Default,,0,0,0,,had the same entrance and just the\Nstalls were different on this side than
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.16,0:14:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,this side. And I thought suddenly dawned\Non me what I thought was morality wasn't
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.24,0:14:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,morality. It's just Puritanism.\NIt's puritinism.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.44,0:14:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,There both sides washed their hands in\Nthe same place. And so
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.24,0:14:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,anyway,\Nwe're persistent. We tend to be open. We
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.16,0:15:00.48,Default,,0,0,0,,tend to be tolerant of differences.\NTolerant of differences, calm,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.48,0:15:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,dependable.\NWe can we tend to be genuine.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.00,0:15:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Respectable means then respecting\Nthe divinity, the sacredness of the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.44,0:15:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,existence of all of life.\NWhen we're respectable, we respect the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.48,0:15:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,black beetle fly lying on its back. We\Nrespect the rights of the animal. We
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.36,0:15:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,respect the life the rights of all of\Nlife to express itself to its most
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.39,0:15:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,favorable degree. And we tend to stand\Nfor that.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.07,0:15:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We tend to be genuine, respectable.\NPatient means not flying off the handle.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.60,0:15:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Now the more evolved we become, the\Neasier it is to become patient and to
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.19,0:15:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,delay delay things. So, as we get more\Nand more right brain,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.39,0:15:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,we slow down. There's a delay. Let me\Nthink about it a second. What color
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.16,0:15:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,shirt do you want? I don't know. I got\Nto think about it a second. So, we drive
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.32,0:16:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,people who are more driven somewhat\Ncrazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.00,0:16:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, get the green one. Well, now I\Nhave to think about it. Here's the one
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.00,0:16:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,with the long lapels. No, no, I got to\Nthink about it. How many buttons? you
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.36,0:16:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,know you have to delay. So the think\Nabout it is really a way to try and
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.83,0:16:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,delay. Why? Because as you get more and\Nmore right brain you slow down with them
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.68,0:16:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and the world is actually going too fast\Nfor you all the time. It's very hard to
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.63,0:16:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,stay rightrain and also keep up with the\Nworld world. Which one? What do you
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.83,0:16:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,want? Blue or green? Blue or green? Come\Non. Give me your answer. You know blue
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.80,0:16:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,or green? What? You know\NI'm still trying to catch up what
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.44,0:16:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,they're talking about. Oh, a shirt. Oh,\Nyou mean buy your shirt. Oh,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.04,0:16:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you're trying to catch up with where\Nthey're at. So, that's a stall. It's a
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.48,0:16:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,ploy. And uh give me a minute. Is uh\Ntime out. So, the more right brain you
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.36,0:17:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,get, the slower you get. In many ways,\Nyou need time out. So, you tend to be
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.72,0:17:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,more thoughtful, more deliberate, also\Ntherefore more patient.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.79,0:17:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I realized I'd learned patience one time\Nwhen I
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.64,0:17:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I had this old truck and it had a plow\Nand and to put the plow on these things
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.88,0:17:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,had to go up there and you had to get a\Nbolt exactly through and there was very
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.00,0:17:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,little clearance. So I took the truck\Nand I went up to the thing and I got out
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.79,0:17:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,bolt wouldn't go through. So I backed\Nthe truck got back again and I moved it
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.31,0:17:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,forward and tried it again. It wouldn't\Ngo.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.60,0:17:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I did that for an over an hour\Nand I finally got it
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.28,0:17:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and I was like sort of ecstatic.\NI said, "You know what? I could do that
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.52,0:17:52.79,Default,,0,0,0,,all day and it wouldn't even bother me."\NIt was like the like a gift. I've got to
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.79,0:17:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,give me a gift. I don't have to have a\Nsome fruits of my action. I don't have
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.24,0:18:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,to be successful.\NYou know what I'm saying? I can just
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.36,0:18:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,fumble it all day long.\NAnd after I learned the lesson, all of a
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.08,0:18:13.12,Default,,0,0,0,,sudden, bang, the boat went in.\NSo many of the things that we rail
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.12,0:18:17.91,Default,,0,0,0,,about, we rail about are gifts from God\Nbecause only by going through that do
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.91,0:18:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you realize that only by having that\Nenergy go out in what was it? The solar
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.44,0:18:28.08,Default,,0,0,0,,plexus of my devote this morning or\Nwhatever it was, the theologian.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.08,0:18:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,only by having it go out in an\Ninconvenient time. Who wants it to go
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.67,0:18:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,out when you're talking to a couple\Nhundred people suddenly you feel his
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.60,0:18:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,energy go out is not convenient.\NNor would it have been recognized if it
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.60,0:18:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,hadn't come up. So it took the energy of\Na whole group like this to bring it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.60,0:18:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how deeply it was buried in the\Nunconscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.64,0:18:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So we're respectful. We tend to be\Npatient and the patience is a
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.72,0:19:02.16,Default,,0,0,0,,consequence of the field.\NIf you try to make yourself patient, it
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.16,0:19:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't work. You know why? Because you\Nget impatient about making yourself
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.48,0:19:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,patient.\NYou get so angry that you can't make
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.76,0:19:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,yourself patient\Nthat you're worse. It better be
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.20,0:19:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,impatient and forgive yourself and let\Nit wear out.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.28,0:19:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,You tend to be stable. You tend to be\Nhonorable. Cordiality. Cordiality is why
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.28,0:19:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,a spiritually evolved person can land in\NNew York City. You walk down the street
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.67,0:19:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and talk to an old lady. You can strike\Nup a conversation with anybody in New
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.12,0:19:37.60,Default,,0,0,0,,York City and instantly become a friend.\NOnce in a while you run into a paranoid
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.60,0:19:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,who goes,\Nbut he's paranoid
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.00,0:19:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,till you say he's paranoid. Poor guy.\NYou tend to be friendly. Therefore, that
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.20,0:20:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,you you're described as mature, you get\Nthat magazine called Modern Maturity.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.55,0:20:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You get to wear a strange thing in your\Nshoes. Moderate maturity has these
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.36,0:20:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,things. Dr. Scho's shoes. These are\Ngenuine Dr. Scholes, by the way,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.64,0:20:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,because they're uh because Dr.\Nofficial's shoes are helpful
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.64,0:20:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and and they're kindly\Neasygoing. They're always the same,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.16,0:20:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,dependable,\Nthey're genuine,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.28,0:20:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,and the company tends to be friendly.\NThey billion in an orderly manner and it
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.79,0:20:43.60,Default,,0,0,0,,all seems normal. So normal. I like Dr.\NScholes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.60,0:20:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see normal is all the way up at\N300.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.60,0:20:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Orderly is a different way of loving.\NOrderly now your caringness extends to
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.44,0:20:57.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the world and to the environment around\Nyou to the environment that you you tend
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.91,0:21:01.12,Default,,0,0,0,,to encounter.\NIf you're orderly, you tend to
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.12,0:21:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,automatically sort of arrange things in\Na more aesthetically balanced way while
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.91,0:21:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,you're on the phone. You're on the phone\Nand you're and you're picking crumbs off
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.24,0:21:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,there and\NDing up the tablecloth while you're
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.48,0:21:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,doing something else.\NIt's hard to stop yourself from
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.32,0:21:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,straightening out the world. I try hard\Nto stop myself, but I just automatically
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.91,0:21:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,have to straighten out the world\Nwherever I go. You see?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.60,0:21:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. So,\Nwe straighten out the world. Uh, we said
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.44,0:21:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,we're friendly, idealistic, and we\Nfinally reached a state called normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.64,0:21:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We say, "I just want a normal person for\Nguy's sake. I'd like to meet, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.28,0:21:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,you get tired of bizarre people that are\Nout in left field with one thing or
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.79,0:21:54.79,Default,,0,0,0,,another. I just want to meet a a regular\Nguy." You know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.79,0:21:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Just a regular person. That's all I\Nwant. Would you like to be with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.79,0:22:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody's just normal, please. Just\Ngive me a regular.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.36,0:22:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody who in better terminology is\Ncalled sane. What we call sane.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.44,0:22:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Sane people are people who agree with\Nus. Of course, everybody knows that.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.72,0:22:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,However, we're willing to be fair and\Ngive them a break and realize that they
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.84,0:22:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,may just have a different view of\Nreality. So, the same person is balanced
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.79,0:22:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can say, I see how they see it\Nthat way. I mean, I can see how Karl
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.12,0:22:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Marx fell into it and he really fell\Ninto it and the world paid a great price
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.76,0:22:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,for Karl Marx's error. If the world had\Ncalibrated Karl Marx before they
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.40,0:22:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,instituted communism in a totalitarian\Nway, they would have saved themselves
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.60,0:22:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,tremendous disaster.\NSo
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.03,0:22:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,sanity then is people that think like\Nus. Fair is the way we treat people and
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.52,0:23:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we hope they will reciprocate.\NEthical of course is who we are. We're
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.00,0:23:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,always ethical. And uh what does ethical\Nmean? It means you live up to your own
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.48,0:23:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,standards to the best of your ability.\NIt also means with the flexibility that
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.03,0:23:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,you won't succeed every time.\NIt means flexibility. You will not
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.15,0:23:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,succeed in being polite, friendly,\Ngregarious, etc. In every instance,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.36,0:23:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,there are times when you won't. However,\Nby this time, your conscience has
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.91,0:23:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,softened so that you don't have to\Nvilify yourself about it. And you can
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.76,0:23:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,say I wasn't at my best.\NI wasn't at my best. So self forgiveness
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.84,0:23:45.12,Default,,0,0,0,,tends to be characteristic.\NWe're ethical. We become flexible.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.12,0:23:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We're balanced. Balance means to try to\Nstay neutral as much as possible. In a
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.48,0:23:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,heavily politicized world, it's it's a\Nconstant task to try and stay neutral.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.79,0:24:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,This side vilifies this side. this side\Nvilifies this side.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.72,0:24:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter who's president, half the\Npeople in the world hate you. I mean, I
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.24,0:24:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,don't know how a person can be\Npresident.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.44,0:24:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The instant you're elected, 40% of the\Npeople hate you already.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.24,0:24:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,I find it hard to sleep with 40% of the\Npeople hating me already. And I haven't
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.24,0:24:23.36,Default,,0,0,0,,even gotten there.\NThey hate you before you even get
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.36,0:24:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,elected, before you even take office,\Ndon't they? And then if you switch
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.40,0:24:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,sides, now the other side hates them.\NRight? First this side hates this side.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.64,0:24:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Then when they switch partners, then\Nthis side hates this side. And after
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.96,0:24:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,you've lived long enough, you get, you\Nknow, it's the same program, the same
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.03,0:24:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,program.\NThis side hates this side and this side
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.40,0:24:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,hates this side. And the details have\Nchanged, but it's frankly the same
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.88,0:24:52.40,Default,,0,0,0,,program. And what good comes out of\Nvilifying your opponent? I'll say to
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.40,0:24:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,political candidates, champion you\Nchampion the one that you want elected
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.84,0:25:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and you don't need to vilify the other\None. Why? You can love chocolate without
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.12,0:25:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,hating vanilla.\NAnd you can love vanilla without hating
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.96,0:25:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,chocolate. Not necessarily to hate the\Nopposer. It's just better to prove that
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.88,0:25:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,you're better than they are. Better than\Nthey are. That you have more to offer.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.96,0:25:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So then people elect you out of love and\Nconsideration.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.48,0:25:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. So you're flexible, you're\Nethical, you're balanced. So that's a
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.79,0:25:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,balanced view which is respectful.\NIt's also healthy. We pointed out this
Dialogue: 0,0:25:30.00,0:25:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,morning\Nthat the negative emotions, the negative
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.32,0:25:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,emotions, Canon's fight or flight\Nresponse is unhealthy. It causes you to
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.03,0:25:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,go weak kinesiologically. It blows out\Nthe acupuncture system. It interferes
Dialogue: 0,0:25:45.76,0:25:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,with the flow of energy through the\Nacupuncture meridians to the various
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.36,0:25:55.91,Default,,0,0,0,,organs of the body. And as you keep\Nblowing out one meridian or another
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.91,0:26:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,repeatedly, eventually you end up with\Norganic physiologic changes in in
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.76,0:26:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,physical illness. So the person who is\Nthen integrous tends to be more healthy
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.00,0:26:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is re more respectful of his life or\Ntheir life and the life of other people
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.64,0:26:18.88,Default,,0,0,0,,tends to be have a more balanced\Nacupuncture and health health system
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.88,0:26:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,altogether.\NFaithful of course is obvious from above
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.84,0:26:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the above sense of humor is more evolved\Nthan I thought it was. I thought sense
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.20,0:26:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,of humor would come up before them\Nbecause there's animals with a sense of
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.96,0:26:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,humor.\NBut a sense of humor to me means the
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.12,0:26:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,piece of people are are you can relate\Nto them. People without a sense of humor
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.32,0:26:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I think are difficult to relate to. Once\Na person can laugh, you're much safer
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.52,0:26:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,with them. Why? Because you can try a\Nthing out in the abstract. Humor comes
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.67,0:26:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,from seeing the thing in the abstract.\NSo you can in humor you can put a thing
Dialogue: 0,0:26:55.36,0:26:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,on in the abstract see it the\Nridiculousness of it and discharge you
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.96,0:27:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,don't have to live it out if you don't\Nhave a sense of humor you have to live
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.48,0:27:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,it out\Nthere people tend to be loyal equitable
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.76,0:27:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,this all evolves into wisdom and at 405\Nwe say the person is reliably rational
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.36,0:27:20.55,Default,,0,0,0,,supportive of others they're benign\Nthey're protective they're humane we can
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.55,0:27:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,trust them they're trustable They're\Ncontent. They're pleasing. Glad. Happy
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.00,0:27:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,to be with you. Sensible.\NSalt of the earth is what we call them.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.96,0:27:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Diplomatic, polite, firm.\NThese are just the basic decencies.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.03,0:27:41.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Basic decencies. But any one of them,\Nyou can see if you practice it around
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.67,0:27:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the clock, seven days a week, you're in\Nand you're out, will automatically
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.27,0:27:50.08,Default,,0,0,0,,transform you to the top of the deck.\NBecause if you're kind and loving
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.08,0:27:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,towards all that exists\Nand you see the beauty, then you begin
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.32,0:27:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to see the beauty of all that exists,\Nyou're already merging into a divine
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.88,0:28:04.72,Default,,0,0,0,,state. So the divine state doesn't have\Nto come as a sudden impact. What it
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.72,0:28:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,means is as you go into spiritual work\Nthen the field becomes predominant. The
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.84,0:28:17.52,Default,,0,0,0,,field to which you're committed begins\Nto influence you not just the ego. So
Dialogue: 0,0:28:17.52,0:28:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,below 200, the person is the victim of\Ntheir own ego. They're the victim of the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.76,0:28:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,evolutionary animal within them.\NFrom 200 and up, now a change takes
Dialogue: 0,0:28:29.91,0:28:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,place physiologically,\Npsychologically, emotionally, in every
